== Biography
Dr. Jingwen Fu graduated from the School of Artificial Intelligence at Xi'an Jiaotong University. During his doctoral studies, he was selected for the joint PhD program between Xi'an Jiaotong University and Microsoft Research Asia (MSRA), where he was supervised by Professor Nanning Zheng and Professor Wenjun Zeng. Additionally, he spent one year as a visiting scholar at RIKEN in Japan, studying under the guidance of Professor Masashi Sugiyama, a renowned scholar in the field of machine learning.

Dr. Fu has long been dedicated to fundamental research in artificial intelligence. His current core research interests focus on the interpretability of Large Language Models, the intersection of LLMs and linguistics, composition generalization, and multi-agent systems. To date, he has published over 10 papers in top-tier international academic conferences and journals in the field of AI and has been granted several national invention patents.

== Research Interest
- Interpretability of Large Language Models
- The intersection of LLMs and linguistics
- Composition generalization
- Multi-agent systems

== Educational Background
- *Ph.D.*, College of Artificial Intelligence, Xi’an Jiaotong University, Sep 2021 – Mar 2026
- *B.S.*, School of Computer Science and Technology, Xi’an Jiaotong University, Sep 2017 – Jun 2021

== For Prospective Students
I am always happy to discuss research ideas with motivated students.  
If you are interested in machine learning theory, LLM understanding, or agent systems, feel free to email me with your background and research interests.
